Constructor:

 Is a block of code similar to method that is executed when we create an object

 Why do we need it?

 => Constructor initializes the object

 How to create a constructor?

1. Constructor name must be same as its class.
2. No return type.

Type of constructors?

1.non argument
2.parametrized

this keyword => is used to refer to the current object
=>this can be used with variables and methods

=>this. used to refer to the instance variables
=>In situation when local variable have same name as instance=> we use this. to differentiate and refer to the instance variable
=>this can be used to refer to the instance methods as well
=> this() it can be used to call CURRENT
 class constructor

=>Default constructor is created by the compiler when a programmer does not create one
